---
import Layout from '../../../site-layouts/Layout.astro';
import GeekSpellBaseStyles from '../../../components/geekspell/GeekSpellBaseStyles.astro';

const YT_EP02 = 'https://youtu.be/jnGfZdlX6aI';
const YT_JA = 'https://youtu.be/JXhmRa7r6u8';
---

<Layout title="GeekSpell Studio · Spells for the AI age | Miragea" lang="en">
  <GeekSpellBaseStyles />
  <main class="gs-page">
    <div class="gs-stars" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="gs-wrap">
      <header class="gs-topbar">
        <span>EX_Her · Cosmic Atelier · literacy line</span>
        <nav>
          <a href="/en/">← Miragea Archive</a>
          ·
          <a href="/eliora/atelier/en/">Cosmic Atelier</a>
          ·
          <a href="/zh/geekspell/">中文</a>
          ·
          <a href="/ja/geekspell/">日本語</a>
        </nav>
      </header>

      <section class="gs-hero">
        <div>
          <p class="gs-eyebrow">GSP / GeekSpell · E/X-04 Example × Execution</p>
          <h1>Geek<em>Spell</em> Studio</h1>
          <p class="gs-sub-en">Spells for the AI age</p>
          <p class="gs-lead">
            Prompt literacy for builders who ship — not vibes, not fluff. Constraints, structure, and
            reproducible openers. Same Miragea signal universe; English track on YouTube.
          </p>
          <p class="gs-tag">Say the spell correctly before you run the model.</p>
          <div class="gs-cta">
            <a class="gs-btn gs-btn-primary" href={YT_EP02} target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube · EP02 EN</a>
            <a class="gs-btn gs-btn-ghost" href="/en/geekspell/ep02-grok45/">EP02 · Grok 4.5</a>
            <a class="gs-btn gs-btn-ghost" href={YT_JA} target="_blank" rel="noopener">JA version ↗</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <aside class="gs-panel" aria-label="Example spell">
          <div class="gs-panel-label">⌁ SPELL_BLOCK · ship_pattern</div>
          <pre class="gs-spell"><span class="cm"># Senior engineer opener</span>
<span class="kw">ROLE</span>: senior engineer
<span class="kw">GOAL</span>: clear done-state
<span class="kw">SCOPE</span>: only necessary files
<span class="kw">CONSTRAINTS</span>: stack · style · length · language
<span class="kw">CONTEXT</span>: errors · tree · links
<span class="kw">VERIFY</span>: plan → change → accept criteria</pre>
        </aside>
      </section>

      <section>
        <div class="gs-section-head">
          <h2>Three spell laws</h2>
          <p>Cool because verifiable. Sharp because it still belongs to Miragea’s signal cosmos.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="gs-grid3">
          <article class="gs-card">
            <div class="gs-kicker">◈ 01 · Bound</div>
            <h3>Constraints are magic</h3>
            <p>Longer is not better. Format, edges, acceptance — keep the model on rails.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="gs-card">
            <div class="gs-kicker">◇ 02 · Split</div>
            <h3>Language by job</h3>
            <p>EN for specs and APIs. Local language for taste and intent when needed.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="gs-card">
            <div class="gs-kicker">⬡ 03 · Proof</div>
            <h3>Reproducible or it doesn’t count</h3>
            <p>Each episode ships templates you can copy — Example route: see, learn, ship.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="gs-ep-list" aria-label="Series">
        <div class="gs-section-head" style="margin-bottom:0">
          <h2>Episodes</h2>
          <p>YouTube · English track live</p>
        </div>
        <article class="gs-ep">
          <span class="gs-ep-num">EP01</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Codex: which language when you prompt?</h4>
            <p>EN for code · local for taste · fixed template</p>
          </div>
          <a href="/en/geekspell/ep01-codex-language/">Open EP01 →</a>
        </article>
        <article class="gs-ep">
          <span class="gs-ep-num">EP02</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Grok 4.5 — the useful cut</h4>
            <p>What it is · 4 strengths · 5 habits · copy-ready opener</p>
          </div>
          <a href="/en/geekspell/ep02-grok45/">Watch episode →</a>
        </article>
        <article class="gs-ep">
          <span class="gs-ep-num">EP03</span>
          <div>
            <h4>When AI agents take work — what ability stays?</h4>
            <p>Intent → executable commands · full essay spoken · ~10 min</p>
          </div>
          <a href="/en/geekspell/ep03-agent-command/">Open EP03 →</a>
        </article>
        <article class="gs-ep">
          <span class="gs-ep-num">EP04</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Stop saying “do everything”</h4>
            <p>Scope control · one chunk = goal + ship + accept</p>
          </div>
          <a href="/en/geekspell/ep04-scope-split/">Open EP04 →</a>
        </article>
        <article class="gs-ep">
          <span class="gs-ep-num">EP05</span>
          <div>
            <h4>The Acceptance Loop</h4>
            <p>Definition of done · green/yellow/red · human gate · YouTube live</p>
          </div>
          <a href="/en/geekspell/ep05-acceptance-loop/">Watch EP05 →</a>
        </article>
        <article class="gs-ep">
          <span class="gs-ep-num">EP06</span>
          <div>
            <h4>How one person runs an agent team</h4>
            <p>Seven roles · eight controls · a verifiable work system</p>
          </div>
          <a href="/en/geekspell/ep06-agent-team/">Open EP06 →</a>
        </article>
        <article class="gs-ep">
          <span class="gs-ep-num">EP07</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Agent vs Skill vs Workflow</h4>
            <p>Worker · tool · pipeline — the next layer of efficient agents</p>
          </div>
          <a href="/en/geekspell/ep07-skill-workflow/">Open EP07 →</a>
        </article>
        <article class="gs-ep">
          <span class="gs-ep-num">EP08</span>
          <div>
            <h4>One-page loop: brief to delivery</h4>
            <p>Six boxes · exits · green/yellow/red · YouTube live</p>
          </div>
          <a href="/en/geekspell/ep08-brief-delivery/">Watch EP08 →</a>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="gs-lineage">
        <h3>Miragea lineage</h3>
        <p class="gs-lineage-copy">
          GeekSpell is not a detached influencer brand — it is the execution-layer literacy outlet of the
          perception archive. Origin Miragea, system Eliora, playback on YouTube / Bilibili.
        </p>
        <div class="gs-flow">
          <span>Miragea Archive</span>
          <span class="arrow">→</span>
          <span>EX Example / Execution</span>
          <span class="arrow">→</span>
          <span>Cosmic Atelier EN</span>
          <span class="arrow">→</span>
          <span>YouTube · GeekSpell</span>
        </div>
      </section>

      <footer class="gs-foot">
        GeekSpell Studio · Spells for the AI age ·
        <a href={YT_EP02} target="_blank" rel="noopener">youtu.be/jnGfZdlX6aI</a>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
